  "title": "Construction Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<p>• Attend tender interviews</p>\n<p>• Provide support activities in procurement, attend</p>\n<p>site meetings, monitoring deliveries and keeping</p>\n<p>track of the entire project timeline</p>\n<p>• Undertake cost analysis for project work</p>\n<p>• Assist in establishing a client's requirements and</p>\n<p>undertake feasibility studies</p>\n<p>• Perform risk, value management and cost control</p>\n<p>• Prepare and analyse costing for tenders</p>\n<p>• Prepare tender and contract documents, including</p>\n<p>bills of quantities with the client</p>\n<p>• Provide advice on contractual claims</p>\n<p>• Responsible for taking off measurement and</p>\n<p>monthly progress claim.</p>\n<p>• Analyse outcomes and write detailed progress</p>\n<p>reports</p>\n<p>• Value completed work and arranged payments</p>\n<p>• Maintain awareness of the different contracts in</p>\n<p>current use</p>\n<p>• Ensure the construction project is completed within</p>\n<p>its projected budget.</p>\n<p>Job Requirement</p>\n<p>• Min Diploma in Quantity Surveying</p>\n<p>• Required language(s): English</p>\n<p>• At least 2 Year(s) of working experience in the</p>\n<p>related field is required for this position especially</p>\n<p>Landscape/ Construction Industries.</p>\n<p>• Required Skill(s): quantity surveyor, project</p>\n<p>management, site coordination, progress claims,</p>\n<p>project costing, contracts</p>\n<p>• Preferably Junior Executive specialized in Quantity</p>\n<p>Surveying or equivalent.</p>\n<p>• Knowledge of contract administration &amp; tender</p>\n<p>procedures is an advantage</p>\n<p>• Relevant experience in Landscape/ Constructions</p>\n<p>industry preferred</p>\n<p>Working Time:</p>\n<p>• 5.5 Working days per week</p>\n<p>• 9am – 6pm</p>",
